## Description {#details}

A materialization unit for symbol aliases.

Allows existing symbols to be aliased with alternate flags.

Definition at line 706 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h">Core.h</a>.

<SectionDefinition>

## Public Constructors

### ReExportsMaterializationUnit() {#aab64c7f0c4f378e1fa034cd086a1bd1a}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::orc::ReExportsMaterializationUnit::ReExportsMaterializationUnit (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> &#42; SourceJD, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a7cb1d8cb0ab2329f032d69d79498c81d">JITDylibLookupFlags</a> SourceJDLookupFlags, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#adfa7bcc2544e48c4531ebfe74ae622b2">SymbolAliasMap</a> Aliases)</>}>
SourceJD is allowed to be nullptr, in which case the source <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> is taken to be whatever <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> these definitions are materialized in (and MatchNonExported has no effect).

This is useful for defining aliases within a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

Note: Care must be taken that no sets of aliases form a cycle, as such a cycle will result in a deadlock when any symbol in the cycle is resolved.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h/#l00716">716</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h">Core.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp/#l00301">301</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp">Core.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
